<TITLE> Adviser invites Delwar to informal talks for Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 22 (bdnews24.com) -- A caretaker government adviser has invited a BNP faction led by Khandaker Delwar Hossain to "informal" talks for Wednesday, a BNP leader said. The party's acting office secretary Rizvi Ahmed told bdnews24.com: "One adviser has talked to Khandaker Delwar Hossain today." The talks have been set for a 5pm start at state guesthouse Meghna. BNP's joint secretary general Nazrul Islam Khan said they would join the talks. "We may have a meeting among ourselves ahead of the talks with the advisers," Khan said. Commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman had earlier invited Delwar to the talks by SMS, but the meeting stalled as the BNP leaders did not show up. The pre-dialogue talks, as they are called, are meant to find ways to narrow the ever-growing gap between the government and political parties. bd
